                <Header>Freedom of Information Act (FOIA)</Header>
                <Paragraph>The FOIA (5 USC 552) gives the public right to request records from a Federal agency. An agency must disclose the requested record as long as one of the law's nine exemptions does not shield the information from public disclosure.</Paragraph>
            </EntitySourceOfInformation>
            <EntitySourceOfInformation EntitySourceOfInformationId="2313" SortOrder="13">
